31:48.240 --> 31:52.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The lawsuit is
currently pending
in federal court.

31:52.377 --> 31:57.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With each passing year, new
research validates
a pioneering large-scale study
from the 1990s

31:57.783 --> 32:03.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that found one in four had grown
up in households
with substance abuse, one in
four had been

32:03.054 --> 32:08.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
physically abused, and one in
five sexually
abused. These so-called adverse
childhood

32:08.360 --> 32:14.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
experiences, or ACEs, were found
to predict
a raft of health and social
problems, from

32:14.065 --> 32:18.103 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
adolescent pregnancy to
depression and heart
disease in adulthood.

32:18.136 --> 32:22.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the long term implications of
childhood
trauma become increasingly
clear, cities across

32:22.674 --> 32:26.711 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the country are trying to
understand the kind
of violence happening in their
own communities

32:26.745 --> 32:31.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
along city streets and behind
closed doors.
Local leaders say the next step
is to stop

32:31.616 --> 32:34.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
those traumatic events from
happening in the
first place.

32:34.853 --> 32:40.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Memphis, Tennessee, a city
rich in music
and culture, but marked by
violence and racial

32:40.992 --> 32:45.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
strife, local leaders who
commissioned a survey
to measure childhood trauma were
stunned at

32:45.831 --> 32:51.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the results; 37 percent of
adults in the county
during their youth had witnessed
someone being

32:51.803 --> 32:56.775 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shot or stabbed; 22 percent
witnessed violence
between adults.

32:56.808 --> 33:01.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But what could local leaders do
to spare the
next generation similar anguish?

33:01.513 --> 33:03.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA HOLDEN NIXON, ACE Center
Task Force
of Shelby County: We know that
children are

33:03.648 --> 33:08.086 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
being expelled from pre-K more
frequently
than they are from K-12.

33:08.119 --> 33:12.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Barbara Holden
Nixon, a longtime
social worker, founded the ACE
Center Task

33:13.024 --> 33:17.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Force of Shelby County. She
convened a who's-who
of state and local government
and community

33:17.896 --> 33:23.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leaders to focus primarily on
parenting to
try to prevent trauma from the
earliest ages.

33:23.201 --> 33:27.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA HOLDEN NIXON: There's
not a transition
place until a person gets to
juvenile justice,

33:27.038 --> 33:31.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, all kinds of things
before they really
see another professional,
because we don't

33:31.076 --> 33:32.944 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
have this preventative network.

33:32.978 --> 33:39.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Nixon turned to
Robin Karr-Morse,
a well-known expert on childhood
trauma. She

33:39.050 --> 33:44.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
says parents who themselves
suffered wrenching
childhoods need help learning
better ways

33:44.055 --> 33:45.790 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to raise their children.

33:45.824 --> 33:49.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBIN KARR-MORSE, The Parenting
Institute:
We're putting no blame on the
parents. The

33:49.594 --> 33:56.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
whole idea is just the opposite.
It's to recognize
that those things have happened
to them. It's

33:56.968 --> 34:03.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not, what's wrong with you?
It's, what happened
to you? And then giving them
tools to help

34:03.909 --> 34:05.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
offset whatever that is.

34:05.777 --> 34:12.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Memphis has
started by opening
Universal Parenting Places, free
drop-in centers

34:12.951 --> 34:19.224 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that offer art therapy that help
children
and parents express difficult
emotions.

34:19.257 --> 34:22.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: I rise above.

34:23.028 --> 34:31.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Music classes to
help stressed
families find joy, and
individual counseling

34:31.903 --> 34:39.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to help parents understand their
own trauma
and break the cycle with their
children.

34:39.110 --> 34:44.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kimberly Lawston sought help
after a bitter
divorce to explain the breakup
to help children.

34:44.215 --> 34:47.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the counseling sessions led
Lawston to
reflect on her own childhood.

34:47.585 --> 34:50.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KIMBERLY LAWSTON, Mother: My
mother was a
hollerer, you know, and I didn't
want to be

34:50.722 --> 34:53.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that way, where you were afraid
to come to
me.

34:53.558 --> 34:58.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Now she's learning
new approaches
to parenting, although she's
faced resistance

34:58.463 --> 35:00.332 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from her family.

35:00.365 --> 35:02.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KIMBERLY LAWSTON: At first, it
was a struggle.
It was like a fight, like
pulling teeth, like,

35:02.968 --> 35:07.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
no, that's not how we do it. We
do it this
way. There's nothing wrong with
us, the way

35:07.339 --> 35:09.574 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we raised you. You have to do
what I say.

35:09.607 --> 35:13.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I was like, well, it's not
your world
anymore. It's mine. And I have
to do what's

35:13.812 --> 35:17.115 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
best for me, in order for my --
me and my
children to heal.

35:17.148 --> 35:21.453 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: One of the
Parenting Places
has opened at Baptist Memorial
Hospital for

35:21.486 --> 35:28.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Women, where doctors can refer
parents directly
upstairs for classes and
counseling. The next

35:28.593 --> 35:31.062 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will open in Perea Preschool.

35:31.096 --> 35:35.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Principal Alicia Norman says
interventions
are urgently needed, as the
number of preschoolers

35:35.900 --> 35:37.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
being expelled grows.

35:37.669 --> 35:41.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALICIA NORMAN, Principal, Perea
Preschool:
They're angry. They are out of
control, 3-

35:41.339 --> 35:45.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and 4-year-olds. And it breaks
my heart to
see that a child has been broken
so early

35:45.643 --> 35:47.412 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in life.

35:47.445 --> 35:51.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: In school surveys,
Norman says
parents report spanking their
children, in

35:51.116 --> 35:54.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
some cases with belts and
electrical cords,
up to five days a week.

35:54.953 --> 35:58.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALICIA NORMAN: For a lot of our
families,
their first option, sometimes
their only option

35:58.056 --> 36:02.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is to spank their children,
where research
shows now the adverse effects of
spanking,

36:02.560 --> 36:04.329 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
especially spanking gone wrong.

36:04.362 --> 36:07.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They want their children to be
the best that
they can be, but these are the
only tools

36:07.465 --> 36:09.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that they have.

36:09.234 --> 36:12.303 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: In terms of law
enforcement, we're
seeing more and more of the
effects that it

36:12.337 --> 36:14.539 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has on children, just violence
in the home.

36:14.572 --> 36:18.910 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: Local law
enforcement officers
say children living in turbulent
homes, whether

36:18.943 --> 36:23.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they're wealthy or poor, are
more likely to
end up in the criminal justice
system.

36:23.515 --> 36:25.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHEN BUSH, Shelby County
Chief Public Defender:
What if we could right-size our
criminal justice

36:25.917 --> 36:27.719 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
system?

36:27.752 --> 36:30.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: But Stephen Bush,
Shelby County
chief public defender and a
fervent member

36:30.488 --> 36:35.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the task force, says the ACE
research is
changing how cases are
prosecuted here.

36:35.460 --> 36:40.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHEN BUSH: The use of adverse
childhood
experiences and the language
around that has

36:40.165 --> 36:44.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
given us a new common language
when we're
advocating on behalf of kids in
front of the

36:44.602 --> 36:50.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
courts that helps explain some
of the behaviors
that might not seem
understandable if you're

36:50.041 --> 36:55.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just looking at it without
understanding the
history of this child's life.

36:55.947 --> 37:00.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Support for this
new awareness
reaches to the top of county
government.

37:00.151 --> 37:05.290 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Shelby County Mayor Mark
Luttrell, also a
task force member, calls the ACE
research

37:05.323 --> 37:07.092 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a basic philosophy of county
government.

37:07.125 --> 37:10.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK LUTTRELL, Shelby County
Mayor: We have
tried to make it the common
thread that runs

37:10.428 --> 37:15.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
through our public safety
agenda, through
our public health agenda,
through our community

37:15.333 --> 37:20.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
services agenda, through our
education agenda.

37:20.271 --> 37:26.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every portfolio that we have
within county
government has a component in
there for, how

37:26.711 --> 37:32.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do you address the younger
generations at
that formative stage?

37:32.050 --> 37:36.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: No one expects
change to come
quickly to Memphis. It could
take decades

37:36.821 --> 37:44.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to figure out if this approach
